         <div type="commentary">
            <p>A tombstone separated into four quadrants by a cross. A hemispherical depression (2 cm deep) destroyed the center of the cross; possibly the stone saw secondary use as a door socket. The two letters of the top line could abbreviate the name Ἱωάννης (as is common in this group), however, no obvious name begins with the letters ΕΣ of the second line. Alternatively, read clockwise, the inscription yields the abbreviation Ἰωσέ for Ἰωσέφος, Joseph.</p>
         </div>
